Bitcoin (BTC): The world's first decentralized currency¶

  • October 31, 2008, a link to a paper authored by Satoshi Nakamoto titled Bitcoin: A Peer-to-Peer Electronic Cash System was posted to a cryptography mailing list and the first block was mined on January 3, 2009

Key Features¶

  • Governance: Decentralized, Balances: Blockchain

  • Transactions: Private Keys, Processing: Mining

How it works¶

  • Network of connected computers known as nodes
  • Cryptographically secure transactions are broadcast
  • Miners (nodes) gather up transactions into a block, validate and relay to other nodes
  • Miners solve a math problem SHA256 Hash (one-way encryption) to verify a block and receive a reward

Importance and Issues¶

  • Bitcoin (BTC) is the largest cryptocurrency in existence today with a market capitalization of $174.5bn as of February 19, 2020

  • For perspective, the market value of Bitcoin is larger than 468 of the companies in the S&P 500 index

  • The blockchain is immutable, all transactions are verified and published publicly creating a wealth of metrics to analyze the network

  • The volatility of Bitcoins price has been a major issue as well as misinformation

Current Trends¶

Cryptocurrency Market¶

  • The Bitcoin halving in May 2020
  • 633,021 wallets (2.7%) hold 16,775,770 BTC (95.4%)

Bitcoin Weekly Price Chart¶

BTC Chart by TradingView

Key Question¶

Is the value of the network the driving factor behind Bitcoin's price?¶

  • Can we identify changes in the network value using on-chain metrics and translate these into a signal that identifies the directional trend of Bitcoin prices for use in an algorithmic trading strategy

  • After all, over $1.0bn is traded daily between investors thus making for an extremely compelling use case

Proposed Product¶

Signal¶

  • A weekly trend signal using on-chain metrics that provides a Long or Short Direction prediction for the upcoming week

Value¶

  • A signal with high accuracy and recall is very valuable to end users including investors, traders, miners, service providers, and researchers involved with the blockchain industry

Implementation¶

Data collection¶

  • Data validation performed comparing Quandl, Glassnode, CoinGecko, Blockchain and CryptoCompare API data prior to selecting Quandl and Glassnode
  • Data consists of historical daily price data from 2014-04-15 to the present day
  • On-chain metrics historical data ranges vary with minimum of 8 years of daily data
  • 30 API endpoints

Data Exploration¶

  • Active Addresses, Unrealized Profit & Loss, Velocity, UTXO, Active Supply, Exchange Flows, MVRV Ratio, Spent Output Profit Ratio, BTC Circulation and Miner Hashrate

Feature Engineering¶

  • Daily data was resampled into weeky data and converted to percentage change
  • Features include Stock-to-Flow, Active Addresses-to-Active Entities and Moving Averages
  • Top Features are the Weekly Change in Unrealized Profit & Loss and MVRV Ratio

# Sequential Timestep LSTM
model = Sequential()
model.add(LSTM(28, input_shape=(X_train_seq.shape[1], X_train_seq.shape[2])))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))
# model.add(Dense(20, activation='relu'))
# model.add(Dropout(0.3))
model.add(Dense(4, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
# fit network
history = model.fit(X_train_seq, y_train_seq, epochs=139, batch_size=39, validation_data=(X_test_seq, y_test_seq), verbose=0, shuffle=False)
# Score the model
tslstm_score = model.evaluate(X_test_seq, y_test_seq, verbose=0)
print('Test score:', tslstm_score[0])
print('Test accuracy:', tslstm_score[1])
model.summary()
# plot history
plt.plot(history.history['loss'], label='train')
plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'], label='test')
plt.legend()
plt.show();

Automated Order Execution System¶

XBT Chart by TradingView
  • The signal is integrated into the indicator module of the automated order execution system that enters 3 to 4 long or short orders based on the signals output
  • Orders are placed hourly based on a computation for liquidation levels of leveraged positions

Results and Summary¶

  • Performance since the signal was created using RFC & TS-LSTM from 1-8 to 2-16 is +32.7% v BTC +21.8% in the live account and from 2-17 to 2-20 using the fully automated TS-LSTM is +5.0% v BTC -3.2% in the test account
  • The monthly pricing of the APIs ranges from Glassnode USD39 (limited access) to USD599 for full access to TokenAnalyst at USD799 and ITB at POR
  • Data this costly validates enterprise demand

Future Work¶

  • Experiment with more complex Neural Networks used in reinforcement learning
  • Extract the average leverage of BTC Perpetual Swaps using K-Means for clustering of the exchange orderbook data
